This paper discusses recommender systems, which are commonly studied in the information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the need to incorporate the interests of multiple parties in recommendation algorithms, which could fall under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the evaluation of these multistakeholder recommendation systems, which could fall under the sub-category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
